# AI Watch — AlphaSignal News Agent

Daily Python worker that scans the AlphaSignal news API, detects new article publications, and emails an AI-generated digest.

## Tech stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Language | Python 3.11 |
| Web retrieval | httpx (official news API + `/news/...` article pages) |
| Summarization | OpenAI (configurable model, default `gpt-4o-mini`) |
| Observability | LangSmith (`@traceable_step`) |
| Memory / dedup | SQLite via SQLAlchemy |
| Email | Generic SMTP |
| Scheduler | APScheduler (internal daily cron) |
| Health API | FastAPI + Uvicorn |
| Packaging | Docker (persistent `/data` volume for SQLite) |

## Agent pipeline

```
APScheduler (daily) → AlphaSignalAgent.run()
  → httpx POST: api.alphasignal.ai/api/news
  → archive_parser: extract title + /news/... URL + publish_time from each row
  → PublicationMemory.find_unseen_since()   ← SQLite dedup
     ├─ Already seen → return status=skipped, no email
     └─ New → httpx GET: alphasignal.ai/news/...
              → archive_parser: extract articleDetails HTML
              → newsletter_parser: highlights + detailed items + links
              → NewsletterSummarizer (OpenAI)
              → SmtpEmailSender
              → PublicationMemory.mark_seen()
  → LangSmith traces every step via @traceable_step
```

## Directory layout

```
backend/app/
  core/config.py          # pydantic-settings, all env vars
  db/database.py          # SQLAlchemy engine (lazy, cached)
  models/seen_publication.py
  services/
    tracing.py            # configure_langsmith(), @traceable_step
    alphasignal/
      agent.py            # AlphaSignalAgent orchestrator
      archive_parser.py   # parse news API rows + article page HTML
      newsletter_parser.py
      memory.py           # PublicationMemory (SQLite)
      summarizer.py       # OpenAI
      email_sender.py     # SMTP
      alphasignal_client.py
  jobs/
    scheduler.py          # APScheduler + FastAPI startup
    run_daily_alphasignal.py  # one-shot CLI entrypoint
  main.py                 # GET /health  POST /run-now
shared/schemas/alphasignal.py  # ArchiveEntry, NewsItem, NewsletterDigest, RunResult
tests/backend/
Dockerfile / docker-compose.yml
.env.example
```

## Key conventions

- All secrets come from `.env` / environment; never hardcode them.
- `DATABASE_URL=sqlite:////data/ai_watch.db` inside Docker; mount `./data:/data`.
- Dedup key = `sha256(url | title | published_at.isoformat())`.
- Every new service step must be wrapped with `@traceable_step("step_name")`.
- Official news API body: `{"page":1,"limit":N,"sort":"latest","timeframe":"latest"}`.
- `RUN_ON_STARTUP=true` triggers an immediate run when the container starts.
